📣 Casting – Statyści do filmu (retro, rok 1999)
📍 Warszawa, Odrębna 
📅 Nagrania: 17.12 od 09:00 do ok 12:00 
💰 Wynagrodzenie 120 zl netto, płatne po planie 

Poszukujemy statystów kobiet i mężczyzn do filmu z retrospekcją czasową, którego akcja rozgrywa się w 1999 roku. Sceny dotyczą przesłuchań DEA, dlatego zależy nam na osobach o odpowiednim, profesjonalnym wyglądzie z tamtego okresu.
🔎 Kogo szukamy?
Kobiety i mężczyźni w wieku 30-50 lat
Naturalny, klasyczny wygląd – zgodny z końcówką lat 90.
Naturalne włosy, bez nowoczesnych koloryzacji
W przypadku kobiet: delikatny makijaż, brak sztucznych rzęs, krótkie lub naturalne paznokcie w neutralnych kolorach.
W przypadku mężczyzn: preferowany gładki zarost lub lekki kilkudniowy, bez pełnej brody.
Mile widziane osoby o „urzędowym”, biurowym typie urody z epoki lat 90.

📩 Zgłoszenia: PAULINA@SCENERIA.COM.PL dopisek DEA 
Prosimy o przesłanie:
imię i nazwisko
wiek
aktualne zdjęcie twarzy + sylwetki
numer telefonu

**SERIAL FABULARNY LALKA **

19.12.25 Piątek  - Łódz 

**EPIZOD AKTORSKI - NIEMY **

Panowie 25 - 40 Lat 

**STAWKA USTALANA INDYWIDUALNIE **

**Panowie:**

– męskie fryzury nie mogą być strzyżone maszynkami , tylko nożyczkami

– nie było włosów podgolonych, były one raczej dłuższe w różny sposób zaczesywane

– mogą być u Panów baki i wąsy.

– brody (nie mogą to być współczesne barberowe brody)

– naturalne kolory włosów bez farb i odsiwiaczy

Zgłoszenie ( imię, nazwisko, wiek, wzrost, rozmiar ubrania nr. tel. Wizytówka w postaci linka do you tube oraz aktualne zdjęcie twarzy oraz sylwetki proszę przesłać na adres **jarek.drzycimski@podtytulem.pl** z dopiskiem w tytule **AKTOR **

Discovery is coming—it’s only a matter of time. When it happens, someone’s getting one hell of a return on their investment.
Question is: who’s bold enough to move first? 🔥
Live loud. Own it. 🔥

items.text:
📘 Brochures That Speak Louder Than Words

In a world dominated by digital noise, a well-crafted brochure cuts through the clutter and creates a lasting impression.

At CF7, we specialize in brochure design that:

✓ Captures attention instantly
✓ Communicates your brand story effectively
✓ Converts prospects into customers
✓ Reflects premium quality and professionalism

From corporate profiles to product catalogs, event brochures to service guides – we design print materials that your audience will actually keep and refer back to.

🎭✨ **We’re in full swing of panto season!** ✨🎭  

The lights are up, the costumes are sparkling, and the laughter is echoing through the theatre. There’s nothing quite like the magic of pantomime—where boos, cheers, and “He’s behind you!” become the soundtrack to December nights.  

Our cast and crew are bringing the festive fun to life with energy, silliness, and heart. From dazzling dance numbers to cheeky jokes that get the whole family giggling, we’re loving every moment of sharing this tradition with you.  

👏 Thank you to everyone who’s joined us so far—you make the magic complete. And if you haven’t yet, don’t miss your chance to be part of the joy. Panto season only comes once a year, and we’re soaking up every sparkle of it!

items.text:
Start 2026 the right way: book your audition and commit to the training that will turn you from “someone who acts” into an actor who succeeds.

At 𝐌𝐚𝐫𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐀𝐜𝐚𝐝𝐞𝐦𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐒𝐰𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨𝐧, 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫, we don’t just run drama classes – we train serious, committed actors for real careers in film, TV and theatre.
We are a multi-award-winning drama academy, proudly holding both the 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 & 𝐍𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐡 𝐖𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐠𝐞 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐃𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐚 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐘𝐞𝐚𝐫 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓/𝟐𝟔 and the 𝐄𝟐 𝐌𝐞𝐝𝐢𝐚 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐃𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐚 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐘𝐞𝐚𝐫 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓/𝟐𝟔, as well as being a 𝐔𝐊 𝐒𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐁𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬 𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓 finalist, representing Manchester in the 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐒𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐁𝐮𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐬 category.
We’re also recognised by 𝐒𝐩𝐨𝐭𝐥𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭, the UK’s leading casting platform, for our professional standard of training.
_____________________________________________________

𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐮𝐚𝐥𝐥𝐲 𝐁𝐮𝐢𝐥𝐝𝐬 𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐫𝐬:

At Marble Academy, you don’t just “do drama classes” – you train like a working actor.
Under award-winning tutor Christian Le Feuvre, you’ll focus on:
• 𝐒𝐜𝐫𝐢𝐩𝐭 & 𝐬𝐜𝐞𝐧𝐞 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐤 – breaking down text like a pro
• 𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐭𝐞𝐜𝐡𝐧𝐢𝐪𝐮𝐞 – self-tapes and in-room auditions that stand out
• 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐞𝐫 & 𝐞𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 – truthful, layered performances
• 𝐎𝐧-𝐜𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐫𝐚 𝐬𝐤𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐬 – marks, continuity and confidence
• Professional mindset – how real actors work, prepare and behave.

You’ll not only improve the talent you already have – you’ll unlearn bad habits, stop doing the things that hold so many actors back, and replace them with sharp, reliable technique.

Whether you’re just starting or ready to level up, this is where you turn “I’d love to act” into “I’m building a real career.”
_______________________________________________________

𝐌𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐧 𝐚 𝐂𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬: 𝐀 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐇𝐮𝐛:

That’s not all—Marble Academy produce award-winning films, hosts interactive workshops, extremely popular networking events for actors and filmmakers, and provides invaluable casting opportunities for our students. We take immense pride in the accomplishments of our graduates, many of whom have gone on to star in acclaimed projects.
______________________________________________________

𝐀𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 & 𝐄𝐧𝐫𝐨𝐥 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟔:

If you’re ready to take your craft seriously:
1. Visit [www.marbleacademy.co.uk](https://www.marbleacademy.co.uk)
2. Check out all the information and read our reviews
3. Apply for an audition and make 2026 the year you stop “thinking about it” and actually do something for your future as an actor.
___________________________________________________

𝐃𝐎𝐍’𝐓 𝐁𝐄 𝐀𝐍 𝐀𝐂𝐓𝐎𝐑 𝐁𝐄𝐂𝐀𝐔𝐒𝐄 𝐘𝐎𝐔 𝐖𝐀𝐍𝐓 𝐓𝐎; 𝐁𝐄 𝐀𝐍 𝐀𝐂𝐓𝐎𝐑 𝐁𝐄𝐂𝐀𝐔𝐒𝐄 𝐘𝐎𝐔 𝐇𝐀𝐕𝐄 𝐓𝐎.

items.text:
**Casting Call for Student Documentary on Route 66**

This film is about America and its diverse perspectives. Want to be part of a thought-provoking documentary that explores the binaries of America through authentic voices along the legendary Route 66?

**About the Project:**
This student documentary will explore the contrasts and contradictions of American life through intimate audio conversations along Route 66. I interviewed all of the subjects, but I need their writing brought to life. From the experiences of gun owners and mothers coping with loss, to casual exchanges with local residents.  The project will be shared on my YouTube and Twitter accounts, reaching over 175,000 followers with 21 million monthly impressions. It will also be submitted to film festivals for wider recognition.

**Roles We’re Casting:**
1. **Mother & Son in a Restaurant (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Mother and her young son (roughly 4-7 years old)
   * **Context:** A lighthearted scene in a restaurant where the son desperately wants ice cream, and the mother is doing her best to manage his request.
   * **Looking for:** A warm, authentic voice for the mother and a lively, eager voice for the son.
2. **Ice Cream Shop Employee (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Ice cream shop employee (any age)
   * **Context:** Serving an ice cream order. Looking for a friendly, upbeat voice.
3. **Mother Discussing Open Carry Laws (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Female (mid-30s to late 40s)
   * **Context:** A mother who has lost a child to gun violence reflects on her thoughts about open carry laws. There is a deep emotional nuance here, as she discusses the pain that still lingers but how she has learned to live with it.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys both strength and vulnerability.
4. **Gun Owner Discussing the Second Amendment (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A proud gun owner shares his thoughts on the Second Amendment and the importance of preserving it. This is a candid, passionate conversation.
   * **Looking for:** A voice with conviction and a strong sense of personal belief.
5. **Elderly Woman Discussing Life in Arkansas (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Elderly woman (60s+)
   * **Context:** After checking out at a store, we strike up a conversation about the area she lives in Arkansas. Looking for a soft, warm, and welcoming voice with a touch of nostalgia.
6. **White Male Discussing Living Near a Reservation (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** White male (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A casual conversation about his thoughts on living near a Native American reservation. This should be an honest, straightforward reflection.
   * **Looking for:** A genuine, no-nonsense voice.
7. **Woman Discussing Love & Lost Love (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Female (20s-40s)
   * **Context:** A woman reflects on her thoughts about love and shares the story of a long-lost love.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys emotion, perhaps tinged with a little melancholy or longing.
8. **Man Discussing Love & Lost Love (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (20s-50s)
   * **Context:** A man reflects on his own experience with love, potentially speaking of a past relationship or lost love.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys sincerity and emotion, with some depth.
9. **Monastery Contact (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (any age)
   * **Context:** A phone conversation where a person from a monastery describes the place to us. Looking for a calm, peaceful, and contemplative voice.
10. **Gas Station Worker (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (any age)
   * **Context:** A person at a gas station reacts upon realizing we’re from Chicago. This should feel spontaneous, with a touch of local pride or curiosity.
   * **Looking for:** A friendly, open voice.
11. **Man Discussing Local Grocery Store (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (30s-60s)
   * **Context:** A casual conversation where a man talks about how far the nearest grocery store is, and the challenges of getting there.
   * **Looking for:** A down-to-earth, conversational voice.
12. **Gas Station Owner Discussing History & Business (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (teens-young adult)
   * **Context:** A conversation with a gas station owner (White) who runs a Native American-themed gas station. They reflect on their role in the business and the history behind it.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys respect for history, but also a practical, no-nonsense attitude about business.
13. **Man Discussing Thoughts on America (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male, southern accent if availible (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A man talks candidly about his thoughts on America, its identity, and what it means to him.
   * **Looking for:** A thoughtful, reflective voice that can express a deep connection to the country.

**Details:**
* **Unpaid** but you'll receive credits in the documentary.
* Your performance will be showcased across my social platforms (YouTube, Twitter) with substantial exposure (175,000+ followers, 21M+ monthly impressions).
* The documentary will also be submitted to film festivals for wider recognition.
* All recordings will be done remotely (via phone or other online means).

**To Apply:**
Please send a message about which role you are interested in helping with.

I'm excited to bring together a diverse group of voices for this project and can't wait to hear from you!
items.summary:
**Casting Call for Student Documentary on Route 66**

This film is about America and its diverse perspectives. Want to be part of a thought-provoking documentary that explores the binaries of America through authentic voices along the legendary Route 66?

**About the Project:**
This student documentary will explore the contrasts and contradictions of American life through intimate audio conversations along Route 66. I interviewed all of the subjects, but I need their writing brought to life. From the experiences of gun owners and mothers coping with loss, to casual exchanges with local residents.  The project will be shared on my YouTube and Twitter accounts, reaching over 175,000 followers with 21 million monthly impressions. It will also be submitted to film festivals for wider recognition.

**Roles We’re Casting:**
1. **Mother & Son in a Restaurant (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Mother and her young son (roughly 4-7 years old)
   * **Context:** A lighthearted scene in a restaurant where the son desperately wants ice cream, and the mother is doing her best to manage his request.
   * **Looking for:** A warm, authentic voice for the mother and a lively, eager voice for the son.
2. **Ice Cream Shop Employee (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Ice cream shop employee (any age)
   * **Context:** Serving an ice cream order. Looking for a friendly, upbeat voice.
3. **Mother Discussing Open Carry Laws (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Female (mid-30s to late 40s)
   * **Context:** A mother who has lost a child to gun violence reflects on her thoughts about open carry laws. There is a deep emotional nuance here, as she discusses the pain that still lingers but how she has learned to live with it.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys both strength and vulnerability.
4. **Gun Owner Discussing the Second Amendment (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A proud gun owner shares his thoughts on the Second Amendment and the importance of preserving it. This is a candid, passionate conversation.
   * **Looking for:** A voice with conviction and a strong sense of personal belief.
5. **Elderly Woman Discussing Life in Arkansas (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Elderly woman (60s+)
   * **Context:** After checking out at a store, we strike up a conversation about the area she lives in Arkansas. Looking for a soft, warm, and welcoming voice with a touch of nostalgia.
6. **White Male Discussing Living Near a Reservation (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** White male (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A casual conversation about his thoughts on living near a Native American reservation. This should be an honest, straightforward reflection.
   * **Looking for:** A genuine, no-nonsense voice.
7. **Woman Discussing Love & Lost Love (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Female (20s-40s)
   * **Context:** A woman reflects on her thoughts about love and shares the story of a long-lost love.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys emotion, perhaps tinged with a little melancholy or longing.
8. **Man Discussing Love & Lost Love (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (20s-50s)
   * **Context:** A man reflects on his own experience with love, potentially speaking of a past relationship or lost love.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys sincerity and emotion, with some depth.
9. **Monastery Contact (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (any age)
   * **Context:** A phone conversation where a person from a monastery describes the place to us. Looking for a calm, peaceful, and contemplative voice.
10. **Gas Station Worker (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (any age)
   * **Context:** A person at a gas station reacts upon realizing we’re from Chicago. This should feel spontaneous, with a touch of local pride or curiosity.
   * **Looking for:** A friendly, open voice.
11. **Man Discussing Local Grocery Store (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (30s-60s)
   * **Context:** A casual conversation where a man talks about how far the nearest grocery store is, and the challenges of getting there.
   * **Looking for:** A down-to-earth, conversational voice.
12. **Gas Station Owner Discussing History & Business (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male (teens-young adult)
   * **Context:** A conversation with a gas station owner (White) who runs a Native American-themed gas station. They reflect on their role in the business and the history behind it.
   * **Looking for:** A voice that conveys respect for history, but also a practical, no-nonsense attitude about business.
13. **Man Discussing Thoughts on America (Audio Only)**
   * **Role:** Male, southern accent if availible (30s-50s)
   * **Context:** A man talks candidly about his thoughts on America, its identity, and what it means to him.
   * **Looking for:** A thoughtful, reflective voice that can express a deep connection to the country.

**Details:**
* **Unpaid** but you'll receive credits in the documentary.
* Your performance will be showcased across my social platforms (YouTube, Twitter) with substantial exposure (175,000+ followers, 21M+ monthly impressions).
* The documentary will also be submitted to film festivals for wider recognition.
* All recordings will be done remotely (via phone or other online means).

**To Apply:**
Please send a message about which role you are interested in helping with.

I'm excited to bring together a diverse group of voices for this project and can't wait to hear from you!

Ich habe Deutsch erst im Erwachsenenalter gelernt. Das hat mich gelehrt: Authentisch und glaubwürdig auftreten geht nur, wenn man ehrlich spielt: die Kamera sieht alles!

In diesem VHS-Kurs zeige ich alle Tools, die ich selbst entwickelt habe, um in einer Fremdsprache selbstbewusst aufzutreten und dabei wahrhaftig zu spielen.

Du darfst dir die Fremdsprache aussuchen: Spanisch, Deutsch, Englisch oder Katalanisch.

Wann: 31. Januar und 1. Februar 2026 in Berlin

Wenn es für Euch resoniert, Plätze sind begrenzt! Anmeldung unter:

 https://www.volkshochschule.de/kursfinder.php?id=vhs-berlin-neukoelln-spielend-selbstbewusst-sprechen-in-film-alltag-fuer-nicht-muttersprachler-innen~11003777964

Ich bin für jedes teilen dankbar! 🌟🙏

📸 Jeanne Degraa 

H & M Birgit Düvelmeyer

#vhskurs #vhsberlin #spielen #SelbstbewusstSprechen

Vielleicht willst du einfach vhs Deutscher Volkshochschul-Verband nur spielen, oder du vermeidest bestimmte Situationen im Alltag, weil du glaubst, die Sprache nicht gut genug zu beherrschen. Ein Gefühl von Machtlosigkeit und Kleinsein übernimmt deinen Kopf und hindert dich daran, deine Authentizität als Mensch und Schauspieler*in zu zeigen.'

Die neue Essenz-Methode ist nicht einfach eine weitere Schauspieltechnik. 

 

Die Methode basiert auf:
* 15+ Jahren Casting- & Kamera-Erfahrung
* Coaching von hunderten Darstellern
* Erfolgen, die Menschen in Filme, Serien, Preise & Chart-Songs gebracht haben

 

Sie vereint alles, was du wirklich brauchst um vor der Kamera zu strahlen. 

Strukturiert, gegliedert und direkt umsetzbar. 

 

Im Workshop lernst du:

✔ wie du Energie vor der Kamera aufbaust

✔ wie du berührst statt spielst

✔ wie du Blockaden löst

✔ wie du dich authentisch zeigst

✔ wie du deine Wirkung nutzt, um Caster und Regisseure WIRKLICH zu überzeugen. 

 

📆 **Early Bird gilt nur noch bis 10.12, 23:59 Uhr. **

Der günstigste Preis, den es bei uns je für einen Workshop geben wird ;-) 

💬 **Kommentiere ESSENZ**, wenn du den Link willst.

Wir schicken ihn dir persönlich.

items.text:
Hi All,

I am new to this group so thought I would introduce myself.  I’ve been acting for about four years. For the first three, I also attended acting school and took separate improv classes.  My training focused mainly on the Meisner technique, with Method acting as a core part as well, and I find both approaches extremely helpful.

Most of my work so far has been outside Portland, where I’m based, but I’m working to do more local projects, but very open to roles outside the Portland area as well.

St Pauls MTC needs you!

Based in Wallasey, St Pauls Musical Theatre Company are thrilled to bring the Wirral debut of The Great British Bake Off Musical to Wallasey - the birthplace of our very own Paul Hollywood!

After a largely successful audition process, we are still in need of a fabulous young actor to take on the role of Hassan.

Hassan is the youngest contestant in the tent - a spirited sixth-form student from Wembley. He’s cheeky, optimistic, and full of energy, bringing humour and warmth to the competition while showing resilience and heart as he bakes under pressure.  

If you have the following performance traits -- 

●Tenor vocal range with rapping abilities.
●Good comic timing and a playful acting style.
●Playing age of 17. Actual age at least 16+.
●We strongly encourage actors from a global majority background to audition.

-- then please contact Sue our Society Secretary at stpaulsmtcsecretary@gmail.com for audition information.

Rehearsals will be held at on Tuesdays (and possibley Wednesdays, tbc) 7:45pm-9:45pm at:
Grosvenor Ballroom Children's Annex
Grosvenor Street
Wallasey
CH44 1AQ
There will be some Sunday rehearsals as we approach the performance dates.

Performances will be:
24th-26th April 2026
Grosvenor Ballroom
Wallasey
CH44 1AQ

sharedPost.text:
the wait is over! we are now accepting submissions for our summer production of “Be More Chill!”

for full details, visit the link in our bio.

Simone Nathalia - Director/Choreographer
Taylor McKee - Music Director
Madison Raybould - Choreographer
Morgan Da Silva-Rolph - Stage Manager

Music and Lyrics by Joe Iconis
Book by Joe Tracz
Based on the Novel by Ned Vizzini

audition dates
in-person: December 20th & 21st, 2025
callbacks: January 3rd, 2026
self-tapes: submissions due on Dec. 19th

audition venue:
Carousel Theatre for Young People, 1411 Cartwright St, Granville Island

audition requirements:
all roles in this production are volunteer, non-union. xoxo welcomes performers 18+ of all genders, ethnicities, and skill levels to audition.

what to prepare:
1. 2 contrasting musical theatre songs, (you may only be asked to sing one, but please have both ready).

2. a 1-2 minute contemporary, comedic monologue - this must be memorized.

how to apply:
please email your headshot and resume to theatre@xoxotv.ca to be scheduled with an audition time, or to request a self-tape submission.

character breakdowns can be found in our “audition package” link in bio.

production dates:
July 15th - 18th, 2026

production venue:
Firehall Arts Centre, 280 E Cordova St, Vancouver

notes:
rehearsals will begin April 30th, 2026
Saturdays 10:00am to 6:00pm
Tuesdays & Thursdays 6:00pm to 10:00pm

contact info@xoxotv.ca or DM us with any questions!

best of luck to all performers - we’ll see you at auditions! 😁💄🐾

BE MORE CHILL is presented by arrangement with Concord Theatricals.
www.concordtheatricals.com
The world premiere production of Be More Chill was commissioned and originally produced by Two River Theater Company in Red Bank, NJ
John Dias, Artistic Director / Michael Hurst, Managing Director
This work was supported by a Theatre Commissioning and Production Initiative grant from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation
Orchestrations and Arrangements by Charlie Rosen
.
.
.

I wanted to share our WhatsApp community that brings together people from different roles — creatives, actors, musicians, managers, and organisers.

The goal is to share perspectives and give feedback across different backgrounds, because that’s often where the most useful insight comes from. Whether you need a self-tape reader, want feedback on new work, or just want to connect, this is a space to share, ask for guidance, and support each other.

HAPPY FRIDAY!

Here's a few creative reminders!

-The last Filmmaker Social of the year, hosted by Tricky Ink Productions at True West Film Center in Healdsburg, will be FRIDAY, DECEMBER 19TH, 6-9PM! ONE WEEK FROM TODAY! However! If you're unable to make it to this event, but you want updates on future events, email me and I'll add you to the mailing list!

[https://truewestfilmcenter.org/show/filmmaker-social-5/](https://truewestfilmcenter.org/show/filmmaker-social-5/)

-I have an actor database, and offer casting services to Directors and Producers.

-I run a Discord server for filmmakers and actors that is very active! There are channels for job posting, casting calls, events, and networking!

-I have a lot of projects and efforts planned for the new year! Filmmaking Workshops in Santa Rosa. A feature film in Petaluma. Short films all over the Bay Area. And more!

If you're an ACTOR looking for more work, a WRITER with a short script, an industry veteran looking to host a workshop, a PRODUCER looking to support a project, or a STUDENT just starting off, reach out! Let's bring more work to the Bay Area in 2026!

[Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com](mailto:Mhamlee.ac@gmail.com)

items.text:
**Actors!, improve your craft. Free cinematography and lighting workshop this Saturday in Los Angeles.**

To Apply and receive a complementary class, email info@empoweringfilmmakers.org

**Unlock Your Filmmaking Potential:**

• Step onto a professional film set, gaining real-world experience while receiving guidance from seasoned instructors who are committed to your success. Be part of a film crew and make movies!

• Immerse yourself in a vibrant and supportive community that empowers filmmakers to build connections and elevate their careers. Make friends for life.

• Dive into hands-on workshops with cutting-edge digital cinema cameras and lighting equipment, bringing your creative vision to life like never before.

• Gain exclusive access to our state-of-the-art studio, along with multiple stunning filming locations that will transform your projects into visual masterpieces.

• Take advantage of free networking events featuring industry luminaries, where you’ll have the chance to meet fellow filmmakers and gain invaluable insights.

• Learn from industry veterans as they visit our studio, providing exclusive training sessions and mentorship opportunities that can shape your future in film.

• Complete our intensive courses and earn a completion certificate that showcases your dedication and skills.

info@empoweringfilmmakers.org

**LOCATION:** Los Angeles, CA, USA
**PRODUCTION DATE:** Monday 12 January 2026 (3–4 hour call)
**PAID, UNPAID OR PROFIT SHARE:** Paid – **$200/hr**
**PRODUCER OR PRODUCTION COMPANY:** Mama Bear Los Angeles
**HOW TO APPLY:** Visit [https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls](https://actorsandextras.com/casting-calls) for casting details.

🎬 **CASTING – MALE TALENT FOR SKINCARE EXTRACTION TUTORIAL (PAID)**

Production is seeking **male talent** in Los Angeles for a skincare extraction tutorial video. This is a short, well-paid shoot ideal for those comfortable having their skin professionally treated on camera.

ROLE REQUIREMENTS

We’re looking for:
* Fitzpatrick skin types **IV–VI**
* **Visible skin texture or bumps**
* **Blackheads/whiteheads on the nose area**
* **Oily skin** preferred
* Age **20–55**

Talent must be comfortable having close-up shots of their face and nose area while a professional performs skincare extractions.

‼️**CASTING CALL**‼️

Für meine Bachelorarbeit suche ich eine Darstellerin für die Hauptrolle HELENA in einem interaktiven Kurzfilm (Drama).
**Beschreibung:**
Helena befindet sich in einer Phase körperlicher und geistiger Erschöpfung. Sie versucht, in ihrer Wohnung Hinweise zu finden, die ihre Situation erklären. 
Die Rolle erfordert eine sehr fein nuancierte Darstellung von innerer Spannung, Orientierungslosigkeit und körperlicher Schwäche und das nahezu ohne Dialog und überwiegend in Nah- und Detailaufnahmen.

Der Film ist nicht linear aufgebaut, das bedeutet: die Zuschauer treffen Entscheidungen, die zu unterschiedlichen Szenenverläufen führen.

**Wo?:** bei 92224 Amberg
**Wann?:** 1 bis 2 Tage im Januar (genaues Datum folgt nach Abstimmung)
**Gage:** Aufwandsentschädigung nach Absprache

**Anforderungen:**
Spielalter: ca. 25 bis 40 Jahre alt
starkes nonverbales und körperliches Ausdrucksspiel

**Bei Interesse bitte einreichen:**
Foto + ggf. Showreel
kurze Info zur Person und Verfügbarkeit im Januar

**Mail an: kurzfilmoth.amberg@gmail.com**

‼️Casting Call! ‼️

Wir suchen einen Darsteller oder eine Darstellerin im Alter von ca. 40–50 Jahren für einen Image- und How-to-Dreh im handwerklichen Bereich. 🔨

‼️Anforderungen:
– authentisches Auftreten
– handwerkliches Geschick (bitte keine zwei linken Hände)
– Freude am Thema DIY/Handwerk
– kleine Sprechrolle vor der Kamera
– Standort: idealerweise NRW, bevorzugt Großraum Düsseldorf

Drehtag in NRW, voraussichtlich im Dezember oder Januar/Februar.
Option auf regelmäßige Folgeprojekte.

‼️Bitte bewerbt euch mit:
– Fotos
– Gagenerwartung für 1 Drehtag
– kurzem Video, in dem ihr eine kleine handwerkliche Tätigkeit ausführt.

Kommentiere mit "Düsseldorf" um den Bewerbungslink zu erhalten! ❤️

items.text:
Die neue Essenz-Methode ist nicht einfach eine weitere Schauspieltechnik. 

 

Die Methode basiert auf:
* 15+ Jahren Casting- & Kamera-Erfahrung
* Coaching von hunderten Darstellern
* Erfolgen, die Menschen in Filme, Serien, Preise & Chart-Songs gebracht haben

 

Sie vereint alles, was du wirklich brauchst um vor der Kamera zu strahlen. 

Strukturiert, gegliedert und direkt umsetzbar. 

 

Im Workshop lernst du:

✔ wie du Energie vor der Kamera aufbaust

✔ wie du berührst statt spielst

✔ wie du Blockaden löst

✔ wie du dich authentisch zeigst

✔ wie du deine Wirkung nutzt, um Caster und Regisseure WIRKLICH zu überzeugen. 

 

📆 **Early Bird gilt nur noch bis 10.12, 23:59 Uhr. **

Der günstigste Preis, den es bei uns je für einen Workshop geben wird ;-) 

💬 **Kommentiere ESSENZ**, wenn du den Link willst.

Wir schicken ihn dir persönlich.

items.text:
CASTING CALL (ulønnet)

Til et kortfilmsprojekt med arbejdstitlen “VISIT” søger vi 3 skuespillere til bærende roller

🗺️ AARHUS

🗓️ 5. - 10. FEBRUAR (+ bufferdag 11. februar)

FRIDA (Hovedrolle)

Spillealder: 22-28

MARCEL (Hovedrolle)

Spillealder: 20-28

DEN FREMMEDE (Bærende bi-rolle)

Spillealder: 24-30

OM FILMEN:

Frida og Marcel er begge midt i tyverne og er begge på hver sin måde gået i stå i tilværelsen. Frida føler, at hun sidder fast i sit ellers billedskønne og perfekte parforhold, og Marcel er lige blevet dumpet af pigen, han troede var sit livs kærlighed.

I to parallelle handlingsforløb kaster de sig ud i to vidt forskellige forsøg på at genfinde gnisten i den grå tilværelse, på to forskellige dates, i to forskellige lejligheder på hver sin side af en opgang.

Vi er støttet af Aarhus Filmværksted, men er stadig en lavbudget-produktion drevet af passionerede frivillige. Projektet er derfor ikke lønnet, men produktionen dækker transport, samt måltider og forfriskninger på set.

📧 Send en mail til [visitkortfilm@gmail.com](mailto:visitkortfilm@gmail.com) med titlen “Casting” efterfulgt af dit navn.

Vedhæft et vellignende billede og eventuelt showreel/CV eller lignende - så kontakter vi dig med mere information.

May be a doodle of text that says 'FRIDA Perfekt liv, Perfekt forhold. Fastläst. Succesfuld, ung kvinde. Hun lever i et glansbillede af parforholdslykke og karrieremessig succes. Under facaden er hun rastlos. Playing age: 22-28 Enhver etnicitet On set dage: 5.-8. februar (Mulige pickups d. 11.)'

May be a graphic of text that says 'MARCEL En ung mand. Flot. Privilegeret. Hablos. Marcel forsoger at etablere et nyt liv, men kan knap overskue at skulle indrette sin nye lejlighed. Folsom og loyal, men ogsa passivt famlende, fanget nostalgi. Playing age: 20-28 Enhver etnicitet On set dage: 8.-10. februar (Mulige pickups d. 11.)'

sharedPost.text:
MUSICAL-AUDITION PÅ ”SPAMALOT” 🏆 
Audition på Nyborg Voldspils næste store sommermusical under åben himmel finder sted d. 10.-11. januar 2026 – tilmeld dig nu! Til forestillingen søges ca. 30 skuespillere, sangere og dansere i alle aldre fra 15 år og op til både roller og ensemble. Selve prøveforløbet starter i februar 2026. Du kan nu læse alt om audition og tilmelding på Nyborg Voldspils hjemmeside, hvor man allerede også kan købe billetter til forestillingen: nyborgvoldspil.dk

ANGÅENDE ENSEMBLE, DANS OG KOR: 
Ensemblet medvirker løbende i forestillingen i mange forskellige scener/kostumer og roller/funktioner. Flere fra ensemblet har replik(ker) undervejs. Ønsker man at gå til audition som danser uden at skulle synge eller have replikker i forestillingen, er dette også muligt. Inden for dans er ”SPAMALOT” en af de musicals med det bredeste felt af genrer, lige fra Las Vegas- og Broadway-showdans til cancan, disco, folkedans, jazzballet, cheerleading og step samt meget mere, og derudover byder koreografierne på uendeligt mange komiske indslag og vinkler. Vi glæder os derfor at se mange stærke dansere til audition, uanset om man har erfaring eller ej inden for de individuelle genrer. Går man til audition inden for sang og bliver udtaget til koret blandt rollerne/ensemblet, synger man med på mange af de 24 numre i forestillingen ud over at indgå i mange af de komiske indslag og scener undervejs.

ANGÅENDE ROLLER:
Du kan læse alt om de individuelle roller i forestillingen samt hvad man skal forberede, hvis man går op på en rolle eller som ensemble: nyborgvoldspil.dk

Nyborg Voldspil præsenterer:

items.text:
CASTING CALL

To Kill A Witch (Short Film)

When Margaret and Anna, a mother and daughter, get wrongfully arrested for witchcraft. They have to withstand extreme torture at the hand of an evil witchfinder and a reverend. Being imprisoned together, they cling to each other, finding the only glimpses of hope in their strong bond. Both try to negotiate a deal with James Hawk, the witchfinder, begging him to release the other. 

This script contains heavily emotional topics, including use of torture utensils, sexual abuse  and use of fire. Each scene will be done considering the actor’s safety our first and main priority. And intimacy will be present throughout the whole filming days. If you have any concerns regarding safety, please address us so we can clarify.

If you are interested in any of the roles, don't hesitate to reach out to us. We will give you all further information and instructions. At the first stage of casting,  we ask you to send us a selftape until the 19th of january. Followed by in person auditions the first week of February.

Email Address:  howtokillawitchfilm@gmail.com

Shooting days: 2nd- 7th of April (TBC)

Location: UK (specific location TBC)

Expenses covered.

Short film premiering  at the BFI in June.

Margaret (playing age 30s- 60s): A fierce, positive woman, whose life is ruined by the appearance of a man who accuses her of witchcraft. She can be defined by her commitment to truth and protectiveness, which leads her to confess to a crime she did not commit.

Anna (playing age 18- 25): Anna is a young, innocent woman, who goes to extreme lengths to save her mother, Margaret. Her mother is the most important person in her life. 

James Hawk (playing age 30+): Religious closed- minded confident man, who would go beyond morality to prove the existence of witchcraft. He is the primary antagonist and witchfinder. His obsession is driven by revenge after the death of his wife.

Reverend Johns (playing age 30+): A religious authority supporting James Hawk, the witch hunter. He is afraid of the devil and the existence of witchcraft but grows increasingly suspicious of  Hawks' work throughout Anna's and Margaret's trial.

items.text:
New dates added - Dec 8-19 in Las Vegas. To book go to https://rebrand.ly/freehdsht

FREE HEADSHOT and 1-HOUR SESSION – East Summerlin, Las Vegas

Address sent automatically after booking

Hi! I’m Steve Fogarty, a Las Vegas headshot specialist and owner of EXPO TRAFFIC, where we run large-scale headshot activations for major trade shows (600-700 people over 2.5 days).

I’m currently testing new lighting setups and posing flows for upcoming conventions, and I’m looking for real people to sit for practice sessions in a more relaxed environment. In return for your time, you get a full headshot session and one professional, retouched headshot for free.

**What You Get**
* A 60–75 minute headshot session
* Multiple looks + lighting setups
* A private online gallery
* One edited, retouched image included
* Additional images optional (zero pressure)

**Examples of my retouching**

[https://rebrand.ly/retouching](https://rebrand.ly/retouching)

Why There’s a $20 Fee

It’s not a sales charge. It’s a **non-refundable security deposit and show-up guarantee** that ensures the schedule stays reliable for both of us. The $20 simply confirms your commitment to attend — and your favorite image is still included for free.

How You Get Your Image

After the session:
* We will review your images, and you'll tell me which ones are your favorites that you do not want deleted.
* I will edit and retouch your favorites, then upload them to your private gallery.
* You can download your favorite image using a coupon code (provided).
* You’re welcome to purchase extras, but it’s totally optional.

What to Expect / How to Prepare
* Arrive camera-ready (mirror + restroom available)
* Plan for 3–4 different looks
* Avoid pure white tops if possible
* Relax — I’ll guide you through every pose and expression

Safety + Professionalism
* All public areas are video security-monitored for your comfort and safety
* Private areas (bathrooms, changing areas) are never recorded
* References available by request

You can preview my work here:

[https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots](https://www.expotraffic.com/headshots/las-vegas-headshots)

**Location**

**East Summerlin near Rainbow & Alta**

**Exact address provided after booking.**

**Looking forward to creating something great together!**

**– Steve Fogarty**

**Owner – STEVEN JOSEPH PHOTOGRAPHY | EXPO TRAFFIC HEADSHOTS**

CASTING CALL – BATH

We’re looking for two actors for a 1600s period-drama music video filming in Bath. 
This is an unpaid collaborative project and we’re aiming for atmospheric, experimental, vintage-horror-style performances.

⸻

FEMALE ACTOR (18–30) – “Agnes”

A farmer’s daughter with a wide emotional range, from love to rage.
• Experimental physical performance (no audio recorded)
• Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
• White/European descent
• Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

⸻

MALE ACTOR (18–35)

A wealthy, confident, and devious character who tries to charm Agnes. Includes a scene where he becomes possessed and shifts into a zombie-like state.
• Strong physical storytelling (no audio recorded)
• Period-accurate clothing, minimal/no makeup
• Please send: headshot, showreel, cover letter

⸻

If you fit either brief and are interested, please email coleoakley101@gmail.com to apply with the required materials.

Thank you.

items.text:
Hi everyone!

I've been volunteering in the filmmaking world for about a year now, and I still have a lot to learn. I'm currently offering free showreels to actors based in Yorkshire as a way to build up my camera operating and directing portfolio.

I’ve written lots of new scripts, and I'm planning another showreel day on either the 28th, the 30th of December, or the 2nd of January.

Each showreel will take around 45 minutes to film. I'm happy to pair people up, but if you'd prefer to arrange your own scene partner, that’s absolutely fine too!

If you're interested, please message me or email lizzieluluproductions@gmail.com — I’d love to hear from you! Please only email if you are interested as I have lots of people emailing but then ignoring me when they receive their call times.

Many thanks. x

🎬 Casting Call: Short Film – Psychological Thriller

Production: Short film (psychological thriller)
Location: London
Shoot Dates: Starting 10th January
Compensation: Food & transport provided

We are looking for 2 female actors (18–28) for the following roles:

Roles:
 1. DANI – Early 20s
 • Vulnerable, emotional, expressive
 • Able to portray fear, desperation, and innocence
 • No prior experience required – ideal for boosting your acting portfolio
 2. CHANEL – Early 20s
 • Confident, manipulative, and intense
 • Able to switch between charming and menacing seamlessly
 • No prior experience required – perfect for portfolio-building

Requirements:
 • Comfortable performing intense scenes (simulated violence)
 • Professionalism on set
 • No previous acting experience required

What We Offer:
 • Transport and food provided
 • Opportunity to work on a high-quality short film
 • Material for your acting reel/portfolio

To Apply:
Please send:
 • Recent headshot or clear photo
 • Short bio (include age)
 • Any acting experience (if any)

Email Applications to: zaramchi777@gmail.com
Subject: Casting – Dani or Chanel

Plastic Monkey Films UK (www.plasticmonkeyfilms.com) is searching for the female lead in their third feature film, written and directed by Scott McQuaid *(‘Space Ninjas’, ‘The Heartsmith’, as seen on Amazon Prime, Apple TV+, and Tubi.)*

Set and shot in England, the film surrounds a writer and a girl from a painting. Filming for these roles will commence in Essex & London, in end-July to August 2026.

Please ensure you are based in England and are able to travel to Essex and London with relative ease. 

***Candidates do not have to be naturally blue-eyed. We are searching for a natural beauty with the joyful, captivating essence of the character.***

More info in the graphic below. Please apply via email by sending your headshot and any other relevant information to producer.plasticmonkeyfilms@gmail.com by 16th December 2025. Selected candidates will be contacted.

Thank you! 

Warmest regards,

Alexandria Kay

Producer at Plastic Monkey Films

message.text:
He still thinks this is his era.
Forty years old.
Hanging around like someone’s about to tap him on the shoulder and say “your time’s come.”

This is Callum.
Low level grunt.
Full time hanger-on.
Part time hard man.

In No Gentle Goodnight, Callum isn’t feared.
He’s tolerated.
Useful when someone needs a door standing near.
Disposable when they don’t.

He knows it too.
That’s why he stays.

Get a job.
Or get in the sea.

🎬 Micro-trailer dropping
Try not to laugh.

#NoGentleGoodnight #Callum #WannabeGangster #BritishCrime #CharacterReveal #IndependentFilm #SunnyRunnyProductions

⭐ OFFICIAL CASTING CALL 

Building a Core Acting Team for a New Film/Stage Universe

I’m assembling a core long-term team (like Kevin Hart’s Plastic Cup Boyz / Adam Sandler’s crew) to develop a new film universe plus multiple original projects.

Phase 1:
A small stage adaptation of my book (just to get everyone in sync).

Phase 2:
We turn that story into our first feature film.

Phase 3 and beyond:
Continuous films inside the Frenchie Extended Universe + original projects outside the universe.
Everyone on the core team will be acting, producing, writing, and helping shape future projects together.

Roles Currently Casting (Core Team Only):

Riley (F) – Love interest of the main character. Loyal, grounded, warm energy.

Isabella (F, Puerto Rican) – Fierce, supportive, emotional backbone of the group.

Crumbs (M) – Comedic timing, lovable troublemaker.

Jordan (M) – Serious, loyal, big heart but stern presence.

Marcus (M, Black) – Later-series antagonist; charismatic, powerful, intimidating.

Jimmy/Frenchie (M) – Already cast.

What I need from you:

Send me a 30–45 second video reading a short line for the character you’re interested in.
Nothing fancy — I just need to see presence, expression, and vibe.

What this is NOT:

This is NOT a one-off gig or a “show up, get paid, leave” job.
This is a long-term creative family building something from scratch together.

What this IS:

✔ A team
✔ A pipeline
✔ A chance to grow into acting/producing/directing
✔ Multiple projects ahead
✔ Long-term involvement as the universe expands

If you’re hungry, reliable, and want to build something real — comment INTERESTED and I’ll DM you a line to read.

Let’s build something Buffalo can be proud of. 🔥
— Jimmy

items.text:
**Casting Certified Fitness, Yoga & Pilates Trainers**
**PAID OPPORTUNITY**

Hello everyone!
I’m currently looking for **certified trainers** for an upcoming project with **a major activewear brand**. We are preparing a new series of social-media training videos and are now conducting a **preliminary casting**.

We’re looking for:
• Fitness / functional training coaches
• Yoga instructors
• Pilates instructors
• Stretching / mobility specialists

We welcome trainers of **different ages and backgrounds**, as long as you are certified, experienced, and confident working with beginner-level clients.

The project includes participation in **on-camera training shoots**.
Details regarding filming dates and compensation will be discussed individually with selected candidates.

If you:
• hold valid certifications
• have at least 5 years of teaching experience
• have on-camera experience (a plus, but not required)
• are open to collaboration

— please feel free to **DM me directly**.
When reaching out, include your training specialty and a link to your social media or examples of your teaching.

Looking forward to connecting with talented professionals!

items.text:
Hi! We are LOOKING FOR A MALE ACTOR for a short film here in Budapest, set during World War II, and we aim to shoot over 2 days in late February 2026 in the Hűvösvölgy area.

The title for the film is KITARTÁS. It is a short film set during the Siege of Budapest and is a psychological exploration of the raw emotional cost in war times. The story follows Hungarian soldiers as they face a moral and physical struggle for survival in the last year of the war in Hungary. The role requires fluency in both English (for crew communication/rehearsals) and Hungarian (as the film's dialogue will be in Hungarian).

The short film will be submitted to local and international film festivals🎬

This is a low-budget short film, but it will have a symbolic payment💰

We are looking for a person to play one of the lead roles.

ÁDÁM:

Character Description: A Hungarian soldier under István’s command. Ádám is a man torn between obedience to his orders and the stirrings of his own conscience and guilt. His internal conflict becomes a major turning point in the film.

Requirements:

Male, 25–30 years old.

1.75cm - 1.80cm 

Fit or in a healthy weight

Strong presence

Must speak English and Hungarian fluently

Comfortable performing in outdoor winter conditions.

Strong dramatic ability and emotional range.

If you would like to be considered, please send your headshots, short introduction, and (if available) a showreel or acting CV to:

✉️ contactingdianag@gmail.com

Deadline: 31/12/2025

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 50/2025

LEINWANDCOMEBACK EINES KINDERBUCHKLASSIKERS, BEWÄLTIGUNG EINES TRAUMAS UND INTERVIEWS MIT KINO- UND BÜHNENLEGENDEN

Die Kulthexe ist zurück, BIBI BLOCKSBERG erlebt ein weiteres Abenteuer und mit ihr folgen viele beliebte Charaktere der Kinderbuchreihe.

Gibt es den Bad Santa wirklich? Im Remake des 1984er Films SILENT NIGHT, DEADLY NIGHT gilt es dies herauszufinden. Ob die Neuauflage des Slashers etwas taugt erfahren Sie in unserem Kinomagazin.

Vor kurzem konnten wir im Weinviertel 2 absolute Top Stars der Kleinkunstbühne und des Films interviewen. Welches Alfred Dorfer und Wolfgang Böck über ihre Karrieren und die aktuelle Situation zu erzählen haben, hören Sie nur bei uns 

Weitere Filmtipps und die grössten Movie Xmas Hits,  präsentiert Ihnen Mrs Santa Claus, Sarah Fuchs. 

Mittwoch 10.12.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

sharedPost.text:
SONGS FROM LIFE – 10.01.2026, 
Gesang, der berührt. Geschichten, die verwandeln.
Deutschlandpremiere

Die preisgekrönte Sängerin Stefanie Rummel nimmt das Publikum mit auf eine fesselnde musikalische Reise – von den Pariser Cafés über die Berliner Kabarettbühnen bis in die Clubs Manhattans.
Mit Songs im Stil von Piaf, Weill, Sondheim und eigenen Kompositionen erzählt sie von besonderen Momenten des Lebens – voller Sehnsucht, Humor, Warmherzigkeit und Tiefe.
Als „herzberührend“ und mit „brillanter Bühnenpräsenz“ gefeiert, begeistert sie ihr Publikum in den USA, Großbritannien und ganz Europa – und geht nächstes Jahr erneut in Australien auf Tournee.

★★★★ „Herausragende Stimme“ – TheReviewHub
★★★★ „Eine Offenbarung“ – LondonTheatre1
Ein inspirierendes, berührendes musikalisches Cabaret über das Leben – getragen von Liedern, Persönlichkeit und Storytelling.

Bernhard Lehner begleitet versiert am Flügel.
Sieben Songs stammen von Stefanie Rummel (Text & Musik) Diese Songs wurden in Kooperation mit Tom Schlüter produziert. (Pianist & Musikproduzent)

Ein Abend voller Gefühl, Humor und internationalem Flair

Adresse: Gallus Theater, Kleyerstr. 15, 60326 Frankfurt, T:758060-20
Ticketverkauf:  https://www.gallustheater.de/prog/vob.php?i=27

sharedPost.text:
📣 Casting – Statyści do filmu (retro, rok 1999)
📍 Warszawa, Odrębna 
📅 Nagrania: 17.12 od 09:00 do ok 12:00 
💰 Wynagrodzenie 120 zl netto, płatne po planie 

Poszukujemy statystów kobiet i mężczyzn do filmu z retrospekcją czasową, którego akcja rozgrywa się w 1999 roku. Sceny dotyczą przesłuchań DEA, dlatego zależy nam na osobach o odpowiednim, profesjonalnym wyglądzie z tamtego okresu.
🔎 Kogo szukamy?
Kobiety i mężczyźni w wieku 30-50 lat
Naturalny, klasyczny wygląd – zgodny z końcówką lat 90.
Naturalne włosy, bez nowoczesnych koloryzacji
W przypadku kobiet: delikatny makijaż, brak sztucznych rzęs, krótkie lub naturalne paznokcie w neutralnych kolorach.
W przypadku mężczyzn: preferowany gładki zarost lub lekki kilkudniowy, bez pełnej brody.
Mile widziane osoby o „urzędowym”, biurowym typie urody z epoki lat 90.

📩 Zgłoszenia: PAULINA@SCENERIA.COM.PL dopisek DEA 
Prosimy o przesłanie:
imię i nazwisko
wiek
aktualne zdjęcie twarzy + sylwetki
numer telefonu

🎬 FILM TALK: SOCIAL MEDIA AGENCIES ARE….A SCAM?!

With Maty Young | @youngonestudio

After lending our services to a social media agency in LA, we learned a hard truth: a lot of “social media management” companies are all talk, no real results. Overpriced retainers, buzzwords, fake metrics.

After 8+ years in the industry, I have watched these companies exploit both clients and crews while pretending to deliver growth. Real success online does not come from smoke and mirrors. It comes from storytelling, creativity, and authenticity.

This is part one of a three part conversation on influencers, marketing, and what actually drives real growth.

🌐 youngonestudio.com
🎥 @thatmatyjguy | @youngonestudio

#filmtalk #youngonestudio #matyyoung #filmmakinglifee #CreatorEducation #socialmediamarketing #AuthenticGrowth #CreatorEconomy #filmtalkseries #FilmmakerJourney

‼️Casting Call! ‼️

Wir suchen einen Darsteller oder eine Darstellerin im Alter von ca. 40–50 Jahren für einen Image- und How-to-Dreh im handwerklichen Bereich. 🔨

‼️Anforderungen:
– authentisches Auftreten
– handwerkliches Geschick (bitte keine zwei linken Hände)
– Freude am Thema DIY/Handwerk
– kleine Sprechrolle vor der Kamera
– Standort: idealerweise NRW, bevorzugt Großraum Düsseldorf

Drehtag in NRW, voraussichtlich im Dezember oder Januar/Februar.
Option auf regelmäßige Folgeprojekte.

‼️Bitte bewerbt euch mit:
– Fotos
– Gagenerwartung für 1 Drehtag
– kurzem Video, in dem ihr eine kleine handwerkliche Tätigkeit ausführt.

Kommentiere mit "Düsseldorf" um den Bewerbungslink zu erhalten! ❤️

items.text:
Unpaid actor 

Hello. I am Grace, I am an ametur filmmaking, I am currently working on a mix media horror project called The Haven Institute. I am looking for a male actor to play the role of Young Nigel Harrow (AGE 20-23, set in 90s). This is currently as a backup so I have a range of actors to chose. What is required is that I will send over a block of script lasting around 3 minutes each (currently there are 7) and I will need the actor to film these clips in their time and their own environment. Location doesn't matter. This project is unpaid.

If you are interested or have any more questions please drop me an email at Thehollowreturn@outlook.com 

Diolch

CASTING/CREW CALL – NEW DOCUMENTARY (Los Angeles, Jan/Feb 2026) 
�From a TV Producer with Discovery & History Channel credits. 

I’m currently casting for a new documentary that explores the powerful stories we attach to the objects we treasure most. I’m looking for people who have one meaningful item something that, when held, brings back emotion, memory, or a story that shaped who you are.

Your object could be:
* A family heirloom
* A gift from someone who has passed
* A reminder of a relationship or life-changing moment
* Or simply something that holds deep, personal significance

This project will highlight everyday people and the extraordinary stories behind the things they hold dear.

FILMING:�Los Angeles — January & February 2026
If you have an item that carries emotional weight and a story you're willing to share on camera, I’d love to hear from you.

TO APPLY:�Please get in touch and share a brief description of yourself, your item, and the story behind it. Photos welcome but not required.
Looking forward to hearing your story.

EMAIL: breynolsbri@gmail.com
INSTAGRAM: @bryannareynolds

**Kurzfristig Komparsen gesucht**

**Ort: München Süd**

**Datum: Sonntag, 14.12.2025**

**Zeit: 15:00 bis ca. 16:45**

**Vergütung: 100€**

Für eine kurze Szene in einem Industriefilm suchen wir sehr kurzfristig Kompars*innen in München. Es soll eine Szene bei einem Stehempfang auf einer Dachterrasse gedreht werden. Die Darsteller sollen sich unterhalten, es gibt aber keine Sprechparts, die zu hören wären.

Für Getränke und Verpflegung in Form von belegten Brötchen, Plätzchen, Punsch und Glühwein ist gesorgt. An einem Heizstrahler kann sich aufgewärmt werden.

Einzige Voraussetzung ist ein gepflegtes Auftreten in warmer Business oder Smart Casual Kleidung und eine pünktliche Ankunft nach Abmachung.

Meldet euch gerne für weitere Details per DM, wenn ihr in der Nähe seid und Lust darauf habt. 🙂

topComments.text: PN ging nicht " durch" . Ich wäre gerne mit dabei :-) VG

items.text: Stell dir vor, du wärst bereits besetzt, bevor das Drehbuch geschrieben ist :-) Genau das könnte ich dir hier anbieten. Anfang des Jahres werde ich das Drehbuch für meinen zweiten abendfüllenden Spielfilm fertigstellen - und ich würde mich gerne schon beim Schreiben inspirieren lassen. Vielleicht bist es genau du, den ich für diesen Film noch brauche.  Er wird in einer U-Bahn spielen und es braucht hier noch originelle Typen, männlich, weiblich oder dazwischen, jung, alt, gerne speziell und ungewöhnlich. Wenn dich das anspricht, schreib mich gerne an und erzähl mir von dir - und vielleicht schreibe ich dir quasi eine Rolle auf den Leib :-) Gibt nichts zu verlieren ;-)

Wir suchen (Laien-)Schauspieler:innen zwischen 30–70 Jahren für eine kurze Performance-Rolle auf dem Weihnachtsmarkt in der Markthalle Neun (Berlin).
Für ein kreatives, therapeutisch-ironisches Pop-up spielst du eine klar definierte, fest gescriptete 1–2-Minuten-Interaktion, die du während deiner Schicht wiederholst.
Fokus: souveräne Präsenz, klare Sprache, ruhiger Humor mit satirischem Unterton. Es wird nicht gefilmt. Es ist eine Performance für die Menschen vor Ort.
Eckdaten
• Termin: 14.12.
• Zeiten: 11–18 Uhr
• Vergütung: 22,50 €/h
• Ort: Markthalle Neun, Berlin
• Onboarding: Kurzbriefing + Script vor Ort
Interesse?
Schick uns ein kurzes Profil (Foto, ein paar Sätze zu dir, Verfügbarkeit) an [circular-squad@civocracy.org](mailto:circular-squad@civocracy.org)
Wir melden uns zeitnah zurück.

📣 Casting – Statyści do filmu (retro, rok 1999)
📍 Warszawa, Odrębna 
📅 Nagrania: 17.12 od 09:00 do ok 12:00 
💰 Wynagrodzenie 120 zl netto, płatne po planie 

Poszukujemy statystów kobiet i mężczyzn do filmu z retrospekcją czasową, którego akcja rozgrywa się w 1999 roku. Sceny dotyczą przesłuchań DEA, dlatego zależy nam na osobach o odpowiednim, profesjonalnym wyglądzie z tamtego okresu.
🔎 Kogo szukamy?
Kobiety i mężczyźni w wieku 30-50 lat
Naturalny, klasyczny wygląd – zgodny z końcówką lat 90.
Naturalne włosy, bez nowoczesnych koloryzacji
W przypadku kobiet: delikatny makijaż, brak sztucznych rzęs, krótkie lub naturalne paznokcie w neutralnych kolorach.
W przypadku mężczyzn: preferowany gładki zarost lub lekki kilkudniowy, bez pełnej brody.
Mile widziane osoby o „urzędowym”, biurowym typie urody z epoki lat 90.

📩 Zgłoszenia: PAULINA@SCENERIA.COM.PL dopisek DEA 
Prosimy o przesłanie:
imię i nazwisko
wiek
aktualne zdjęcie twarzy + sylwetki
numer telefonu

items.text:
Witam wszystkich! 

Nazywam się Daria, mam 28 lat i już od 10 lat mieszkam w Warszawie. 
Oryginalnie pochodzę z Ukrainy. 

Aktorstwo od zawsze było moim wielkim marzeniem – już jako dziecko chciałam stać przed kamerą i tworzyć emocje, które poruszają. Dziś, z dużym doświadczeniem jako modelka i pierwszymi krokami na planach filmowych, chcę spróbować w pełni wejść w świat, o którym marzyłam.

Mam za sobą udział w produkcjach „Biała odwaga”, „Dirigente” i wielu innych twórczych projektach, które pozwoliły mi poznać realia pracę na planie i utwierdziły mnie w przekonaniu, że aktorstwo jest drogą, którą chcę podążać.    

Jestem pełna energii, zaangażowania i gotowa na kolejne wyzwania przed obiektywem. Jeśli tworzysz projekt i szukasz kogoś z pasją – chętnie dołączę!

📩 Zapraszam do kontaktu https://www.instagram.com/oh.darja?igsh=MXBjc3g5eW94ZG45MQ==

items.summary:
Witam wszystkich! 

Nazywam się Daria, mam 28 lat i już od 10 lat mieszkam w Warszawie. 
Oryginalnie pochodzę z Ukrainy. 

Aktorstwo od zawsze było moim wielkim marzeniem – już jako dziecko chciałam stać przed kamerą i tworzyć emocje, które poruszają. Dziś, z dużym doświadczeniem jako modelka i pierwszymi krokami na planach filmowych, chcę spróbować w pełni wejść w świat, o którym marzyłam.

Mam za sobą udział w produkcjach „Biała odwaga”, „Dirigente” i wielu innych twórczych projektach, które pozwoliły mi poznać realia pracę na planie i utwierdziły mnie w przekonaniu, że aktorstwo jest drogą, którą chcę podążać.    

Jestem pełna energii, zaangażowania i gotowa na kolejne wyzwania przed obiektywem. Jeśli tworzysz projekt i szukasz kogoś z pasją – chętnie dołączę!

📩 Zapraszam do kontaktu https://www.instagram.com/oh.darja?igsh=MXBjc3g5eW94ZG45MQ==

What an incredible night! A massive thank you to every filmmaker and creative who attended our Colorado Springs Meet-N-Greet on December 6th. The energy was electric, and the connections forged were exactly what these events are for: uniting newbies, veterans, and everyone in between for networking and potential new collaborators!

A special shout-out to Red Leg Brewing Company for being an absolutely amazing venue!

Get Ready, Denver!

The momentum continues! We are thrilled to announce we're heading to the Mile High City. We will be revealing the location and details for our Denver Networking Event happening in January very soon!

Follow us so you don't miss the announcement!

UGC Casting 

2 males (40's - 60's) 

Blue Collar 

30 sec's (70-80 word script) 

Film from home. Prefer you have access to a garage, trades space or vehicle (HVAC, Plumber, electrician ect). 

Pay $100. 

Turnaround 2 days. 

Email or DM if you fit the breakdown (tjlafoun@gmail.com). with a UGC demo reel (if you have one), background photo (can be inside a van/ truck), blue collar photo / headshot. 

Thanks in advance.

message.text:
💰 Price Reduced: $474,900

Welcome to Oak Lane — a beautifully maintained Colonial home that blends classic charm with exceptional potential. Located on one of Brighton’s most peaceful, tree-lined streets, this property offers comfort, elegance, and room to grow.

Situated within the top-rated Pittsford School District, this 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath home is the perfect match for families seeking spacious living, outstanding schools, and long-term stability.

Property Highlights

• 🛏 Bedrooms: 4
• 🛁 Bathrooms: 2.5
• 📐 Living Area: 2,128 sq ft (Public Records)
• 🚗 Garage: Heated, 2-car attached
• 🌳 Lot Size: 0.30 acres
• 📍 Subdivision: Smallwood
• 🏫 School District: Pittsford

❤️ Why This Home Is Truly Special

From the moment you enter, you’re greeted by a warm traditional floor plan enhanced with thoughtful updates, refined finishes, and timeless character.

🪵 First Floor Features

• Bright & inviting living room with elegant Italian tile
• Stunning mirrored accent wall that elevates the light and space
• Cozy family room with walnut wood paneling + custom built-ins
• Beautiful brick fireplace for relaxing evenings
• Sun-filled dining area overlooking the backyard
• Spacious eat-in kitchen with granite counters and abundant storage
• Convenient first-floor laundry + powder room

🛌 Second Floor

All four bedrooms are generously sized and full of natural light:
• Oversized primary suite with private bath + walk-in closet
• Three additional bright bedrooms with premium flooring
• Updated bathrooms with marble flooring and modern fixtures

🏡 Lower Level & Backyard

• Expansive basement, perfect for finishing or storage
• Mature landscaping, a private patio, and ideal entertaining space

This home represents the best of Brighton living — a quiet neighborhood, beautiful surrounding homes, and quick access to East Ave, schools, parks, restaurants, and shopping.

📉 Price Improvement

Recently reduced from $505,000 → $474,900
A rare value opportunity in Brighton and Pittsford School District.

🤝 Interested in a private showing?

I’d be happy to schedule a tour and walk you through every detail.

Andrii Pinskyi

Platinum Properties & Asset Management of Rochester & Upstate NY

items.text:
Genre: Komödie (Kurzfilm) Laufzeit ca. 8min

Gesucht: männlicher Schauspieler für Hauptrolle und bis zu 5 Komparsen und Nebenrollen

Spielalter: Anfang bis Mitte 50

Rollenbeschreibung:

Hauptrolle:

Ein Lehrer in seinen fünfzigern, bereits mit lichtem Haar, klassisch altmodisch gekleidet und eine dazu passende altmodische Einstellung gegenüber dem Schulsystem und den Schülern.

Logline:

Ein unsicherer Lehrer, der vergeblich um Respekt kämpft, wird durch den Spott seiner Schüler so radikal verändert, dass er vom Gutmütigen zum gnadenlos Strengen mutiert.

Nebenrolle:

Schüler:

Spielalter: 18

Ein sensibler und aufmerksamer Schüler, der seinem Lehrer den entscheidenden Rat gibt, damit er von der Klasse respektiert wird.

**Es gibt noch 4 weitere Rollen als SchülerInnen, je nach Bevorzugung als Komparse oder Nebenrolle mit Text** (bitte nur Bewerber ab 18)

Gage: Low-Budget Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden und Fahrtkosten werden erstattet. Alle Bewerber sollten einen direkten Fahrtweg oder eine selbstständige Möglichkeit zur Unterkunft haben, da diese leider nicht gestellt werden kann.

Drehort: Im Großraum Stuttgart, nähe Backnang, im Bildungszentrum Weissach im Tal

Drehzeitraum: 14.01.26-15.01.26

Bewerbung entweder per Mail oder direkt Nachricht.

Kontakt:

Bianca Brandner

E-Mail: brandner.bianca@web.de

Evgeni, a non-speaking little boy living in Russia is told his abusive father is going to be killed. Despite having a chance to save him, he lets his father die to end his torment. 19 years later, Evgeni is put in a position to save another man’s life, though it will cost him his freedom. 

***see casting call poster for more info about characters***

Project: Albatross 
Director: Matey Enchevich
Producer/Co-Producer: Grecia Espinosa Torres & Ava Torres
Shooting dates: Feb 27th - March 1st 2026 (3 days) 
Volunteer Position
Lunch, Snack and drinks provided 

Special note: 
‼️ Actors don’t have to be fluent in ASL but must at least know ASL and are willing to learn 

Send headshots by December 30th 2025 to albatross.filmprod@gmail.com

items.text:
Hello,

My name is Allison and I am the producer for the Student Short Film** “Soundly Awake”** at VFS Film Production Program. We are currently looking for Non-Union Actors to cast in our film!

**Project Title:** Soundly Awake

**Project Type:** Student Short Film

**Union Status: **Non-Union

**Director:** Raj Heer

**Producer:** Allison Wall

**Casting Director:** Allison Wall

**Audition Dates:** Self-tapes due by January 8th, 2026

**Audition Location:** Self-tapes only

**Call Back Dates:** January 11th, 2026

**Call Back Location:** 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2

**Shooting Dates: **January 27th - January 29th  

**Shooting Location:** Greater Vancouver Area

**Rates:** Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to soundlyawakefilm@gmail.com and indicate which role you’d like to be considered for.

**Synopsis:**

Haunted by recurring nightmares of his abusive father, Jun, a lonely and withdrawn man, meets Sage, a curious nightmare eater who appears to “consume” his pain. As Sage helps ease Jun’s suffering in the Between, Jun begins to open his heart, finding the strength to confront his father in the real world. When the nightmares end and Sage has to leave, Jun is heartbroken, fearing he will never see Sage again, until an unexpected reunion proves that some bonds endure beyond dreams.

But when his traumatic father re-enters his life, he begins to have vivid nightmares of his childhood that affect his sleep. He is then put in a rare position where he has to confront his traumas and fears, allowing him to access the ultimate freedom he's always wanted. soundlyawakefilm@gmail.com'

items.summary:
Hello,

My name is Allison and I am the producer for the Student Short Film** “Soundly Awake”** at VFS Film Production Program. We are currently looking for Non-Union Actors to cast in our film!

**Project Title:** Soundly Awake

**Project Type:** Student Short Film

**Union Status: **Non-Union

**Director:** Raj Heer

**Producer:** Allison Wall

**Casting Director:** Allison Wall

**Audition Dates:** Self-tapes due by January 8th, 2026

**Audition Location:** Self-tapes only

**Call Back Dates:** January 11th, 2026

**Call Back Location:** 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2

**Shooting Dates: **January 27th - January 29th  

**Shooting Location:** Greater Vancouver Area

**Rates:** Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.

**Submission Instructions:**

Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel (if applicable) to soundlyawakefilm@gmail.com and indicate which role you’d like to be considered for.

**Synopsis:**

Haunted by recurring nightmares of his abusive father, Jun, a lonely and withdrawn man, meets Sage, a curious nightmare eater who appears to “consume” his pain. As Sage helps ease Jun’s suffering in the Between, Jun begins to open his heart, finding the strength to confront his father in the real world. When the nightmares end and Sage has to leave, Jun is heartbroken, fearing he will never see Sage again, until an unexpected reunion proves that some bonds endure beyond dreams.
